doc_summary_long: A sixth noose has been found in the D.C. area, this time in Southeast - several doors from an elementary school. The hate symbol was found displayed by a front door in the 2100 block of 36th Place SE on Thursday, according to a D.C. police report. The report lists the victims as 'Society/Public.'
doc_summary_short: A sixth noose has been found in the D.C. area, this time in Southeast - several doors from an elementary school.
doc_title: Sixth noose found in DC area near elementary school in Southeast
